The article discusses the importance of preparedness in the face of natural disasters and emergencies. It highlights the various challenges that Americans have faced in recent years, including hurricanes, wildfires, floods, and earthquakes. The article emphasizes the need for individuals, communities, and the government to be prepared and resilient. It mentions the role of first responders and the importance of having an emergency plan, signing up for alerts, and having an emergency fund. The article also mentions the Federal Emergency Management Agency's Ready Campaign, which provides guidelines for preparedness. It concludes with a proclamation from President Donald J. Trump declaring September 2019 as National Preparedness Month and urging all Americans to take action to be ready and resilient in the face of disasters.